# Component Organization

## Placement and boundaries
- Components live under route-local `_components` first; promote to shared only when reused across domains.
- Keep presentational components separate from data-fetching server concerns.
- Keep modal components grouped under `Modals/` within their feature.

## Composition patterns
- Build screens from small feature components (header, list, card, modal) instead of monolith files.
- Pass typed props from `src/app/lib/definitions.ts`.
- Prefer derived display values in helper modules (`typeConversion`, grading helpers).

## Client/server split
- Use `"use client"` only where hooks/event handlers/browser APIs are needed.
- Keep stateful interaction in client components and source-of-truth data in actions/server components.

## Styling
- Prefer Tailwind utility classes in component markup.
- Remove dead CSS imports/selectors after migration.
- Keep shared visual primitives consistent (`whiteBox`, button conventions, spacing rhythm).
